                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-98-victim854 t18180506-98-viclabel556"></join>, in the <placeName id="t18180506-98-crimeloc557">Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180506-98-crimeloc557" type="placeName" value="Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180506-98-crimeloc557" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-98-off554 t18180506-98-crimeloc557"></join>. On the 10th of April, in the morning, I observed 24oz. of tea concealed in a lumber-room below stairs-it was in a handkerchief, which I knew to be the prisoner's; he was our <rs id="t18180506-98-deflabel558" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180506-98-defend852 t18180506-98-deflabel558"></join>. I informed Mr. Peck - We sent him out in order to examine it. I ran down, and found it had been removed - He went down stairs before he went out; I called him back. Mr. Peck charged him with stealing tea - He denied any knowledge of it. We sent for a constable, who searched, and found it in the same room, but in a different place to where I at first found it-it was in a basket, which hung up. I am certain no person but him had been down stairs; nobody could have removed it but him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ARABIN. I never quarrelled with the prisoner - I suspected him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180506-98-person857">
                  SAMUEL 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18180506-98-person857" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
